'''Joel Bogen''' (born 3 September 1958)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.toyah.net/joelfeat.html |title=Dreamscape - Joel Bogen |accessdate=15 February 2009 |author=David Scott Fleming |publisher=www.toyah.net}}</ref> is an [[England|English]] [[rock music|rock]] and [[punk rock|punk]] [[guitarist]].  He worked with [[Toyah Willcox]] from the late 1970s to 1983 as the guitar player in her eponymous band [[Toyah (band)|Toyah]] and was Willcox's co-writer on nearly all of the material that they recorded.

